%% Sequence Diagram: Workflow Kick-Off from Jira-Backed Item (FR-005)

sequenceDiagram
    participant Dev as Developer
    participant CC as Claude Code
    participant Orch as Orchestrator (Backlog Picker)
    participant MCP as Atlassian MCP
    participant Conf as Confluence Cloud
    participant RA as Requirements Analyst
    participant State as state.json
    participant BL as BACKLOG.md

    Dev->>CC: "Let's work on PROJ-1234"
    CC->>BL: Search for PROJ-1234
    BL-->>CC: Found: item 7.7 with Jira metadata

    Note over CC: Determine workflow type
    CC->>MCP: Get ticket type for PROJ-1234
    MCP-->>CC: type: "Story"
    CC-->>Dev: "Starting feature workflow for PROJ-1234: {title}"

    CC->>Orch: /isdlc feature "{title}"

    Note over Orch: Init workflow
    Orch->>State: Create active_workflow with<br/>jira_ticket_id: "PROJ-1234"<br/>confluence_urls: ["https://wiki..."]

    Note over Orch: Phase 01: Requirements
    Orch->>RA: Delegate Phase 01

    Note over RA: Check for Confluence context
    RA->>State: Read confluence_urls
    State-->>RA: ["https://wiki.example.com/pages/spec-123"]

    RA->>MCP: getLinkedDocument("https://wiki...")
    MCP->>Conf: GET page content
    Conf-->>MCP: { title, body }
    MCP-->>RA: { title: "Feature Spec", content: "..." }

    Note over RA: Display Confluence Context Banner
    Note over RA: Inject content into<br/>requirements elicitation stages 1.1-1.5

    RA-->>Orch: Phase 01 complete (informed by Confluence context)
